File: New Zealand rugby player Sonny Bill Williams tweeted his support for the Muslim minority group, echoing beliefs of Arsenal soccer star Mesut Ozil. JOHANNESBURG - New Zealand rugby player Sonny Bill Williams has taken a stand against China's oppression of the Uighurs. READ: Sonny Bill reveals doubts over RWC fitness battle Williams tweeted his support for the Muslim minority group, echoing beliefs of Arsenal soccer star Mesut Ozil. He denounced how the group is being treated, saying more countries should speak out. On his tweet, he wrote: "It's sad when we choose economic benefits over humanity, #Uighurs." China is accused of systematically targeting the Uighurs, incarcerating as many as two million in facilities it describes as "vocational training centres".